      <abstract>
        <p>Howard goldberg reviews Fonseca Bin No 27 non-vintage port wine (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Old-timers love to pass a January evening with a good book, an armchair, fresh walnuts and a warming glass or two of Fonseca Bin No. 27 nonvintage port.</p>
        <p>Sipped slowly, this smooth, sweet red yields lingering flavors of prunes, raisins and spicy fruitcake. It hints at the spectrum of subtler flavors awaiting buyers of vintage-dated ports, which can be expensive.</p>
      </block>
